title: body()
brief: Return the value of the parsed message body.
seealso: header, current_message
version: 0.18
----

<p>When in message-mode, or index-mode, the <span class="tt">body()</span> function may be used to retrieve the parsed body from the currently selected message.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre>
text = body();
</pre>
<p>If you wish you may point the function at a saved message:</p>
<pre>
text = body( os.getenv( "HOME" ) .. "/Maildir/Drafts/cur/1.2.3.txt" );
</pre>
